# Shell scripts must keep LF line endings — a CRLF shebang line breaks
# execution under bash/sh even when the file is only ever edited on Windows.
# Required by .agents/kit-manifest.conf's own note to adopters.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
*.ps1 text eol=lf

# Generated mirrors of .agents/agents/ and .agents/skills/ (see
# scripts/mirror-agents.sh / mirror-skills.sh) — never hand-edited, always
# regenerated from the canonical .agents/ source. Marking them
# linguist-generated collapses their diffs in GitHub's review UI; merge=ours
# prefers the local side on conflict, since the correct resolution is always
# "re-run the mirror script," never a manual line-by-line merge. The
# `ours` driver itself is local git config (`git config merge.ours.driver
# true`) — set that up per-clone if you want the merge=ours attribute to
# actually take effect; .gitattributes alone only declares the intent.
.claude/agents/** linguist-generated merge=ours
.claude/skills/** linguist-generated merge=ours
.codex/agents/** linguist-generated merge=ours
.codex/skills/** linguist-generated merge=ours
.github/agents/** linguist-generated merge=ours
.github/skills/** linguist-generated merge=ours
